==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: gibberellic acid
<hw>gibberellic acid</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>, <def>A plant
growth hormone of the <isa>gibberellin</isa> series
(<chform>C19H22O6</chform>), also called <altname>gibberellin
A<sub>3</sub></altname>. It was first isolated from the fungus
<spn>Gibberella fujikuroi</spn>. It is used to promote the growth of
seedlings. See also <er>gibberellin</er>.</def> <au>MI11</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>gibberellin</ent>⟦br⟧
